Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Boil a large #pot{} of water with a good pinch of @salt{pinch}. Roughly chop the @red potato{1}(roughly chopped) into 2cm chunks. Add your potato to the pot and simmer for ~{15-20%minutes} until you can easily slip a knife through, then drain. Mash your potato with a good pinch of @salt{pinch}, a grind of @black pepper{} and a hearty knob of @butter{} (if you have some), cover and set aside for later.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Chop the @British chicken thighs{6}(chopped into bite-sized pieces) into bite-sized pieces.

Add a splash of @oil{} to a large #frying pan{} over medium heat and add your chicken. Cook for ~{10%minutes} until nicely browned on the outside. Add your garlic and a pinch of @salt{pinch}, sauté for ~{1%minute}, then remove from the pan and pop in a large #ovenproof dish{} (the size of a laptop would be perfect!).

While your chicken is cooking, cut the ends off the @leek{1}(sliced into 1cm wide rounds) and slice into 1cm wide rounds then roughly chop the @tarragon{1/4%bunch}(roughly chopped). There is no need to chop the @button mushrooms{1}(no need to chop unless gigantic ones!), unless you have any gigantic ones!

Once you have transferred your chicken to your dish, add a splash of @oil{} to the same frying pan (no need to wash) and cook your mushrooms for ~{3%minutes} over medium heat. Now add your leek and cook for a further ~{6%minutes} or until everything is nicely browned and starting to soften. Remove the pan from the heat and add your mushroom and leek mixture to your dish.

Add the @chicken stock pot{1}, @creme fraiche{1} and tarragon to your dish and stir everything together. Carefully fold in the @thyme{1/2%bunch}(whole sprigs) and the @bay leaf{1}. Tip: Careful not to eat them later!

Cut the tops off the @tri-coloured chantenay carrots{500%g} then slice your white and purple carrots in half lengthways (no need to peel). Slice your orange carrots into four strips if they are a bit thicker. Place them on a #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and the @honey{2%tbsp}. Sprinkle over some @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together. Pop in your oven on the bottom shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}.

Cover your creamy chicken mixture with your mashed potato. Top with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}, a grind of @black pepper{} and pinch of @salt{}. Pop your dish on the top shelf of your oven for ~{25%minutes}, until nice and golden.

Serve your chicken and mushroom pie with a good helping of honey glazed carrots and enjoy!